        </div>
        <aside class="fullBio todd">
            <a class="close">✕</a>
            <h5 class="name">Todd Presner</h5>
            <h6 class="org">Professor, University of California Los Angeles<br>
            Sady and Ludwig Kahn Director of the UCLA Center for Jewish Studies<br>
            Chair of Digital Humanities Program</h6>
            <p>Todd Presner is Professor of Germanic Languages and Comparative Literature at the University of California Los Angeles.&nbsp; He is the Sady and Ludwig Kahn Director of the UCLA Center for Jewish Studies and is also the Chair of the Digital Humanities Program. His research focuses on European intellectual history, the history of media, visual culture, digital humanities, and cultural geography.&nbsp; His books include: <em>Mobile Modernity: Germans, Jews, Trains</em> (Columbia University Press, 2007), <em>Muscular Judaism: The Jewish Body and the Politics of Regeneration</em> (Routledge, 2007), <em>Digital_Humanities</em> (MIT Press, 2012), co-authored with Anne Burdick, Johanna Drucker, Peter Lunenfeld, and Jeffrey Schnapp; and <em>HyperCities: Thick Mapping in the Digital Humanities</em> (Harvard University Press, 2014), co-authored with David Shepard and Yoh Kawano. His collaborative research has been awarded numerous grants and prizes, including the MacArthur "digital media and learning" prize and a Google Digital Humanities grant.</p>
        </aside>

        <!-- Smith -->
        <div class="person" data-name="mackenzie">
            <img class="image" src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/service-zipper/ucp/images/person-mackenzie-568x658.jpg" alt="MacKenzie Smith bio picture" width="568" height="658">
